## Dependencies
npm install @videoml/player @videoml/stdlib --workspace packages/springstack

The @videoml/player package provides VideomlDomPlayer, a React component that renders VML compositions using a headless DOM player with requestAnimationFrame-based timeline. Zero external runtime dependencies beyond React 18.

## File: packages/springstack/src/fileTypes/VmlContent.tsx

Component:
1. useState for VML XML string content and parsed metadata
2. useEffect to fetch(node.data.url).then(r => r.text()) on mount
3. Parse XML with DOMParser to extract metadata:
   - Root element attributes: id, title, fps, width, height
   - Count <scene> elements for scene count
   - Parse duration from scene timings if available
4. Render: BaseContent wrapper + VideomlDomPlayer component
5. Show metadata section: resolution, fps, scene count, duration

## VideomlDomPlayer Integration
import { VideomlDomPlayer } from '@videoml/player';

<VideomlDomPlayer
  xml={vmlXml}
  width={containerWidth}
  height={containerWidth * (9/16)}  // Maintain 16:9 aspect ratio
  autoPlay={false}                   // Don't auto-play in file browser
  clockMode='bounded'                // Stop at end
  loop={false}
/>

## Metadata Extraction
function parseVmlMetadata(xml: string) {
  const doc = new DOMParser().parseFromString(xml, 'text/xml');
  const root = doc.querySelector('vml, videoml, video-ml');
  if (!root) return null;
  return {
    id: root.getAttribute('id'),
    title: root.getAttribute('title'),
    fps: parseInt(root.getAttribute('fps') ?? '30'),
    width: parseInt(root.getAttribute('width') ?? '1920'),
    height: parseInt(root.getAttribute('height') ?? '1080'),
    sceneCount: root.querySelectorAll('scene').length,
  };
}

## Registry Registration
'application/x-vml+xml': {
  icon: Clapperboard,
  detailLine: (node) => {
    const { width, height, fps, sceneCount, durationSec } = node.data ?? {};
    const parts = [];
    if (width && height) parts.push(width + '×' + height);
    if (fps) parts.push(fps + 'fps');
    if (sceneCount) parts.push(sceneCount + ' scenes');
    if (durationSec) parts.push(formatDuration(durationSec));
    return parts.join(' · ') || undefined;
  },
  content: (node) => <VmlContent node={node} />,
}

