## Dependencies
npm install @hpcc-js/wasm-graphviz --workspace packages/springstack

@hpcc-js/wasm-graphviz compiles Graphviz to WebAssembly, enabling client-side DOT-to-SVG rendering with no server. Supports all Graphviz layout engines (dot, neato, fdp, sfdp, circo, twopi, osage, patchwork).

## File: packages/springstack/src/fileTypes/GraphvizContent.tsx

Component:
1. useState for DOT source string and rendered SVG string
2. useEffect to fetch(node.data.url).then(r => r.text()) on mount
3. useEffect to render DOT to SVG using Graphviz WASM instance
4. Display rendered SVG inline using dangerouslySetInnerHTML (safe since SVG comes from Graphviz, not user input)
5. SVG container with overflow-auto for large graphs

