## File: packages/springstack/src/fileTypes/GenericContent.tsx

Component renders:
1. BaseContent wrapper with icon + title + detail line
2. File metadata section: MIME type, size
3. 'No preview available' message styled in muted text
4. Optional download link: <a href={node.data.url} download>

## Pattern Established
This component establishes the pattern all other file type content renderers follow:
1. Accept SpringstackNode<TData> via slot renderer signature
2. Use BaseContent from registryComponents.tsx for consistent layout
3. Access file data from node.data (url, sizeKb, etc.)
4. Fetch file content from node.data.url if needed (not needed for generic)

## Registry Registration
In apps/demo/src/lib/nodeTypes.ts:
createNodeTypeRegistry<DemoNodeData>({
  fallback: {
    icon: File,
    detailLine: (node) => {
      const parts = [node.data?.mediaType, node.data?.sizeKb ? node.data.sizeKb + ' KB' : null];
      return parts.filter(Boolean).join(' · ') || undefined;
    },
    content: (node) => <GenericContent node={node} />,
  },
})
